quran[6]{c,v,t}:
  7,82,"And his people had no answer except to say, “Turn them out of your dwellings; these are people who wish purity!”"
  7,83,"And We rescued him and his family, except his wife – she became of those who stayed behind."
  7,84,"And We rained a shower (of stones) upon them; therefore see what sort of fate befell the culprits!"
  7,85,"And We sent Shuaib to Madyan from their community; he said, “O my people! Worship Allah – you do not have any God except Him; indeed a clear proof has come to you from your Lord, so measure and weigh in full and do not give the people their goods diminished, and do not spread turmoil in the earth after it is organised; this is for your good, if you believe.”"
  7,86,"“And do not be seated on every road in order to scare the travellers, and to prevent from Allah’s path the people who believe in Him, wishing to distort it; and remember when you were few and He increased your numbers; and see what sort of fate befell the mischievous!”"
  7,87,"“And if a group among you believes in what I have been sent with, and another group does not believe, then wait until Allah judges between us; and Allah’s judgement is the best of all.”"
